      • newIterable

        public ISizedShuffleIterable<T> newIterable(Iterable<String> references)
        Description copied from interface: IShuffleIterable
        Create a new instance of the concrete class that will use the given references as the source of items produced. These references are considered the source for all items produced. If the implementation does any filtering/mutation of the referenced items it is based on these references and must be applied to this set of references. Often called during IShuffleIterable.shuffle() and IShuffleIterable.shuffle(long) with the shuffled references returned by IItemReferenceIterable.getReferences().
        Specified by:
        newIterable in interface IShuffleIterable<T>
        Specified by:
        newIterable in interface ISizedShuffleIterable<T>
        Parameters:
        references - the list of references to serve as a source for the iterable returned by IItemReferenceIterable.getReferences() of this instance and which ultimately produces the items from the iterable. Implementations are free to sub-select from the given list of references, but if they do then this sub-selection must be returned by the implementation's IItemReferenceIterable.getReferences() method.
        Returns:
        never null.
